      "title": "Use substitution to eliminate y",
      "content": "From $8x + y = -11$, we get $y = -11 - 8x$. Substitute into $2x^2 = y + 341$:<br/>$$2x^2 = (-11 - 8x) + 341 = 330 - 8x$$<br/>$$2x^2 + 8x - 330 = 0$$<br/>Dividing by 2:<br/>$$x^2 + 4x - 165 = 0$$"
